      .col-md-12  
        p The dominant color of The Iron Yard Brand is the standard <em>Gray</em> that is used in the Shield Mark. Other major colors in the palette denote sub-brands associated with subjects within the Academy. These are featured in the mext section. Each color has hue progressions associated with it with the middle hue being the dominant variation. Practically, these can be used as tone-on-tone variants of the dominant color and used to add variety to any illustration or layout. These hue variants are used to create the duotone imagery seen in the <a href="#photo">photography section</a>. Sometimes, when creating printed pieces for each of the sub-brands, a darker Shield may be used on top of the sub-brand's base hue. See the header of this web page as an example. It is assumed that most print appications will be executed using 1-color or 4-color process plus a spot for the logo if needed. If you really want to get fancy, the duotones can be created using the two spot colors as well, but it's not necessary. Each hue progression has a callout color associated with it as well. The callout color is used to emphasize the call-to-action in layouts. It should be used sparingly. See the <a href="#examples">files at the bottom of the guide</a> as examples of how the hues can be used in conjunction with each other.
