      .col-md-12  
        p The Iron Yard offers a variety of different subjects for aspiring designers and developers to sink their teeth into. These subjects each have their own unique icons as well as color scheme. This enables each subject to distinguish itself and its topics easily without straying away from the over-arching brand. The icons can be used in both the encapsulating Shield as well as without. The unencapsulated icon is best used when other icons are in the near vicinity as they are on <a href="http://theironyard.com/academy/">this page</a>. The Shield version is best used when standing alone-for instance on a card or brochure that is solely about that particular subject. These uses should be left up to the designer's discretion. Flexibility is needed with the icons in order to best determine usage, but stronger rules will likely develop over time. One hard and fast rule is that if the icons are sharing the same page as The Iron Yard Shield, the icon should never compete with or crowd the logo.
