      .col-md-12  
        p Photography plays an important role in The Iron Yard's branding elements, an it can be used to breathe some life into the different applications of The Iron Yard brand. The main thing to keep in mind when using imagery is that this is the time that you, the designer, can choose to bring in the human element. What is The Iron Yard without the students, instuctors, professionals, and entrepreneurs that hang around the place? They should be featured, and this is the place to do it. Full color imagery reigns supreme on the website, but in print form, the duotone images rule. The website is vast, and there are many many places to pepper images in and around other brand elements. With standard print collateral, you have one brief shot to get the point across, and the strong duotone imagery helps drive that brand recognition deeper into the viewers skull. That may seem a bit intense...but we're an intense bunch sometimes.

